        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 5:20PM CDT by NWS Nashville TN</headline>
        <description>At 520 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Lafayette, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lafayette and Red Boiling Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
